{"id":1892,"date":"2017-09-06T10:13:40","date_gmt":"2017-09-06T09:13:40","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.edlab.org.uk\/?p=1892"},"modified":"2017-09-06T10:14:34","modified_gmt":"2017-09-06T09:14:34","slug":"escape-the-classroom","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/escape-the-classroom\/","title":{"rendered":"Escape the Classroom"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Escape Rooms have become increasingly popular entertainment experiences in recent years, in which groups of people work together to solve puzzles and escape a locked room in a limited time period. As well as developing teamwork, communication and puzzle-solving skills, these rooms have the potential to embed puzzles that are related to specific disciplines or subject areas to provide a playful way for participants to engage with curriculum content.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1893\" src=\"http:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"525\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled4.png 700w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled4-300x225.png 300w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled4-120x90.png 120w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled4-180x135.png 180w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled4-256x192.png 256w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled4-360x270.png 360w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled4-480x360.png 480w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" \/><!--more--><\/p>\n<p>The aim of this project was for students to design, develop, and test a series of escape rooms that would be used as part of a programme of outreach to enthuse potential students about different subject areas. The project team were given the basic training and resources to build educational escape rooms, and given opportunities to test and refine their designs.<\/p>\n<p>Visit students\u2019 blog posts on Environmentalists:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/katysedlab.wordpress.com\/\">Kathleen Daly<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/learningspree.wordpress.com\/2017\/04\/18\/escape-the-classroom-project\/\">Zara Sultan<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\t\t<style type=\"text\/css\">\n\t\t\t#gallery-2 {\n\t\t\t\tmargin: auto;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t#gallery-2 .gallery-item {\n\t\t\t\tfloat: left;\n\t\t\t\tmargin-top: 10px;\n\t\t\t\ttext-align: center;\n\t\t\t\twidth: 33%;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t#gallery-2 img {\n\t\t\t\tborder: 2px solid #cfcfcf;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t#gallery-2 .gallery-caption {\n\t\t\t\tmargin-left: 0;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\/* see gallery_shortcode() in wp-includes\/media.php *\/\n\t\t<\/style>\n\t\t<div id='gallery-2' class='gallery galleryid-1892 gallery-columns-3 gallery-size-medium'><dl class='gallery-item'>\n\t\t\t<dt class='gallery-icon portrait'>\n\t\t\t\t<a href='https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled.png' title=\"\" data-rl_title=\"\" class=\"rl-gallery-link\" data-rl_caption=\"\" data-rel=\"lightbox-gallery-2\"><img width=\"225\" height=\"300\" src=\"https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-225x300.png\" class=\"attachment-medium size-medium\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-225x300.png 225w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-67x90.png 67w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-101x135.png 101w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-144x192.png 144w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-conte